{"lemma":"مُفَتِّح","slug":"مُفَتِّح","root":"ف.ت.ح","root_slug":"ف-ت-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ت-ح","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32891","n32892","n32893"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%AA%D9%90%D9%91%D8%AD"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32891","headword_ar":"مَفْتَحٌ","root":"ftH","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place in which things are reposited, stowed, laid up, kept, preserved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guarded; a repository;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xizaAnapN","text_ar":"خِزَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxozanN","text_ar":"مَخْزَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hoard;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaziynapN","text_ar":"خَزِينَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"treasure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"buried property;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kanozN","text_ar":"كَنْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) pl., in both senses,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafaAtiHu","text_ar":"مَفَاتِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) The pl. as occurring in the Kur xxviii. 76 is said to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"treasures"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"buried property"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kunuwz","text_ar":"كُنُوز"},{"kind":"text","text":") and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hoards"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xazaAy^in","text_ar":"خَزَايِن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaziynapN","text_ar":"خَزِينَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", not of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xizaAnapN","text_ar":"خِزَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]): or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hoards"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xazaAwy^n","text_ar":"خَزَاوين"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which Az says is the most probable meaning: (L, TA:) or it there means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"keys,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mifotaHN","text_ar":"مِفْتَحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Ksh, Bd;) and it is said that they were of skins, of the measure of the finger, and were borne upon sixty mules, (Ksh, L, TA,) or seventy; but this is not a valid explanation. (L, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","L","Ksh"]},{"entry_id":"n32892","headword_ar":"مِفْتَحٌ","root":"ftH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"see the next preceding paragraph, and the next but one following; the latter in two places. ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A conduit"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanaAp","text_ar":"قَنَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n32893","headword_ar":"مُفَتِّحٌ","root":"ftH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a medicine &c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Aperient; having the property of opening the bowels:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufat~iHN lils~udadi","text_ar":"مُفَتِّحٌ لِلسُّدَدِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deobstruent; having the property of removing obstructions."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}